## Sequence documentation

Each checkout flow has a dedicated file in `docs/sequences/`:

| File | Flow |
|------|------|
| checkout.md | Happy path UC-3 → UC-5 |
| cancel.md | Abandon UC-6 |
| expiry.md | Hold expires UC-7 |
| compensation.md | Order fails after hold |
| reconciliation.md | Timeout ambiguous outcome |

### Triggers to update sequences

- New API endpoint affecting checkout flow
- Changed order of saga steps
- New error branch or HTTP status mapping
- Reconciliation logic change

Each sequence file includes:
- Use case IDs
- Mermaid sequence diagram
- Link back to FAILURE-SCENARIOS row
- Phase gate checklist (optional)

**Do not** embed all sequences in ARCHITECTURE.md — link to sequence files instead.

